column168: DRIVER PICKED UP SHIPMENT AT SHIPPERS DOCK AT APPROXIMATELY 3:30 P.M. HE RE TURNED TO THE TERMINAL AT 5:45 P.M.  UPON HIS ENTERING THE TERMINAL YARD, H E DISCOVERED LIQUID COMING OUT OF THE REAR DOOR OF THE TRAILER.  THE DOOR W AS OPENED AND THE CARGO INSPECTED TOI DETERMINE WHERE THE LIQUID WAS COMING FROM.  THE SUPERVISOR ON DUTY DETERMINED THE LEAK WAS FROM ONE OF THE LARG _E TANKS FILLED WITH ACETONITRIL.  HE REPORTED THIS TO ME AND I THEN CALLED CHEMTREC FOR ASSISTANCE.  THIS WAS REPORTED TO THE LOCAL FIRE DEPARTMENT O IN ORANGE CONNECTICUT.  THIS WAS ALSO REPORTED TO THE STATE OF CONNECTICUT OFFICE OF THE D.E.P.  THE FIRE AND POLICE DEPARTMENTS RSPONDED AND ASSISTAN CE WAS RENDERED BY MEMBERS OF A HAZARDOUS TEAM FROM AMERICAN ENVIRONMENTAL TECHNOLOGIES.  THE TEAM DETERMINED THE LEAK WAS CAUSED BY A LOOSE VALVE.  T HEY TURNED OFF THE VALVE AND CONTAINED THE LEAK.  THE SHIPPER WAS NOTIFIED AND RESPONDED TO ASSIST.  THEY PICKED UP THE TANK INVOLVED AND RETURNED THI S TO THEIR FACILITY FOR INSPECTION AND CORRECTION.  THE EAST COAST ENVIRONM ENTAL SERVICE COMPANY WAS CALLED IN TO CLEAN THE AREA.  ALL WATER, SAND AND RESIDUE WA REMOVED IN STEEL DRUMS FOR ANALYSIS AND PROPER DISPOSAL.

THE LEAK WAS ALMOST STOPP ED WHEN IGNITION OCCURED FROM UNKNOWN SOURCE. THREE (3) FIREMEN RECEIVED 1S T AND 2ND DEGREE BURNS AT THAT TIME. THE FIRE WAS EXTINGUISHED WITH FOAM. THE RECOVERED PRODUCT WA S PUMPED INTO THE TERMINAL'S SKIMMER PIT AND THE CONTAMINATED TOP SOIL WAS REMOVED FROM THE SHOULDER OF THE ROAD AND STORED IN TERMINAL YARD PENDING T EST RESULTS.

DRIVER ARRIVED AT GENERATORSFIRST LOCATION AT 5:15 AM 5/20/88. AT THIS LOCA TION, 1600 GALLONS OF CHROMIC ACID SOLUTION (MANIFEST #LA1048369) WAS LOADE D. FROM THIS POINT, WE WENT TO THE SECOND LOCATION TO PUMP APPROXIMATELY 18 DRUMS OF CHROMIC ACID SOLUTION (MANIFEST # LA1037248). THE SECOND LOCATION IS WHERE THE PROBLEM OCCURRED. SOMEHOW, 4 OR 5 DRUMS OF ALCHOL, PETROLEUM BASED MATERIAL WAS MIXED IN WITH THE ACID. THE LINER IN THE TRAILER IS DESI GNED FOR ACIDS ONLY. THE PETROLEUM BASED MATERIAL ATTACKED THE LINER. AFTER THE LOAD WAS IN TRANSIT, THE REACTION IN THE TRAILER FINALLY DESTROYED THE LINER AND BEGAN DETERIORATING THE TRAILER. THE LEAKAGE WAS DISCOVERED IMME DIATELY. THE DRIVER MOVED THE TRAILER FROM THE HIGHWAY TO A VACANT SERVICE STATION. ALL THE APPROPRIATE AUTHORITIES WERE CONTACTED AND A CLEAN UP CREW FROM EMTECH ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICES ARRIVED FOR CLEAN UP. BEALINE SERVICES AND CHEMICAL WASTE MANAGEMENT WERE CONTACTED TO OFF LOAD THE MATERIAL AND T RANSPORT TO TSDF. DUE TO THE PROBLEM WITH THIS DRUMMED MATERIAL, OUR COMPANY WILL NO LONGER C OLLECT MATERIAL UNLES IT IS IN AN OPEN VAT OR LARGE COLLECTION TANK. PLEASE NOTICE ATTACHED PRODUCT SPECIFICATONS ON OUR TRAILER.
